---
/**
 * How it works — three steps, each one a beat in the scroll narrative playing
 * out on the constellation behind this section (brain/index.ts reads the
 * data-beat markers to time the scrub):
 *   connect → the network is the factory's history
 *   search  → a target color enters, retrieval propagates (data-beat="search")
 *   recommend → the matched recipe flares (data-beat="match")
 *   silence → the network dims and stills (data-beat="abstain")
 */
---

<section class="how" id="how-it-works">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="how__head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Live inference · one target</p>
      <h2 class="title">Watch history become a decision.</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        No generated formula. No black-box guess. Color Brain searches what
        your factory has already proven.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ol class="how__steps">
      <li class="how__step reveal" data-beat="connect">
        <div class="how__step-top">
          <span class="how__num">01</span>
          <span class="how__state">Index</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Your production memory, mapped.</h3>
        <p>
          Historical batch records become a living CIELAB map. Substrate,
          process, recipe, and measured outcome remain connected as evidence.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="how__step reveal" data-beat="search">
        <div class="how__step-top">
          <span class="how__num">02</span>
          <span class="how__state">Search</span>
        </div>
        <h3>A new target enters the map.</h3>
        <p>
          Retrieval propagates only through compatible history, finding the
          closest proven recipe on the same substrate and production context.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="how__step reveal" data-beat="match">
        <div class="how__step-top">
          <span class="how__num">03</span>
          <span class="how__state how__state--win">Recommend</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Evidence clears the confidence gate.</h3>
        <p>
          You receive a recipe your factory actually ran, with its batch
          number, measured result, neighborhood evidence, and win probability.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="how__step how__step--silence reveal" data-beat="abstain">
        <div class="how__step-top">
          <span class="how__num">04</span>
          <span class="how__state">Abstain</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Not enough evidence? It stays silent.</h3>
        <p>
          The same gate that makes a recommendation useful also knows when not
          to make one. Calibrated silence is part of the product.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .how {
    position: relative;
    padding-bottom: 15vh;
  }

  .how::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    z-index: -1;
    inset: 0 38% 0 0;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(7, 8, 12, 0.98) 68%, transparent);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .how__head {
    min-height: 48vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    max-width: 31rem;
    padding-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  .how__steps {
    position: relative;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .how__steps::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, transparent, var(--line) 8%, var(--line) 92%, transparent);
  }

  .how__step {
    min-height: 68svh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    max-width: 30rem;
    padding: 2rem 2rem 2rem 2.25rem;
    border-left: 1px solid transparent;
  }

  .how__step-top {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.8rem;
  }

  .how__num,
  .how__state {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.67rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    letter-spacing: 0.13em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .how__num {
    position: relative;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
  }

  .how__num::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: -2.55rem;
    width: 0.58rem;
    height: 0.58rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-faint);
    background: var(--bg);
    transform: translateY(-50%) rotate(45deg);
  }

  .how__state {
    padding: 0.25em 0.6em;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .how__state--win {
    border-color: rgba(70, 199, 154, 0.35);
    color: var(--win);
  }

  .how__step h3 {
    max-width: 14ch;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.65rem, 2.7vw, 2.25rem);
  }

  .how__step p {
    max-width: 29rem;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .how__step--silence h3 {
    color: var(--abstain);
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .how {
      padding-bottom: 5rem;
    }

    .how::before {
      right: 0;
      background: rgba(7, 8, 12, 0.58);
    }

    .how__head {
      min-height: 58svh;
    }

    .how__step {
      min-height: 62svh;
      max-width: 27rem;
      padding-right: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
